<title>UK: First Leisure benefits from bid talk.</title>
<headline>First Leisure benefits from bid talk.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-07-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in diversified leisure group First Leisure Corp Plc climbed on Friday, after the Daily Mail newspaper revived speculation that the company may become a bid target.</p>
<p>The shares were up 7p to 314p by 0802 GMT.</p>
<p>&quot;They have been marked up on rumours of a bid from Rank Group Plc,&quot; said one market-maker.</p>
<p>Shares in Rank, meanwhile, failed to join in the broad market rally and were unchanged at 359-1/2p.  </p>
<p>The newspaper cited rumours that rival leisure giant Rank was about to strike with a hostile bid worth around 400p a share.</p>
<p>First Leisure's recent share price underperformance and deteriorating profitability meant the group looked vulnerable to a bid, the newspaper said.</p>
